    "updated_at": "2015-11-22T15:04:03Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is another side-effect of the IDisable interface (the legacy method for disabling traits on an actor) interacting badly with upgradable traits.  There is a hardcoded check in `Cloak` to not activate if the actor is disabled.\n\nIn order to fix this we need to remove that old interface and change powerdown etc to work using upgrades.\n"
  },
